**Abstract:**
Essay fragment dated May 31, 1993, titled "Theology: From Historia to Scientia." The document examines the 1230-1265 debate over whether theology could be transformed into an Aristotelian science. At that time, theology was identified with "sacra pagina" (the biblical text), so the question was whether the Bible could be couched in scientific terms and judged by Aristotelian standards. The author's hypothesis is that this thirteenth-century shift represents an early episode of the transformation Frei analyzed at the Enlightenment.

**AI Recommendation:** Essay fragment connecting medieval transformation to Frei's analysis; develops the historical dimension of the Chantilly thesis.

